{
    "identity": "nprot-2711",
    "title": "A protocol to improve pluripotent stem cell differentiation",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "Prior to the onset of directed differentiation, pluripotent stem cells are cultured in maintenance medium with 1% or 2% DMSO for 24-48h. Proceed with desired differentiation protocol after this treatment."
        },
        {
            "header": "Troubleshooting",
            "content": "Please see the supplementary note included in our publication \\(PMID: 23584186) for additional suggestions on optimization."
        },
        {
            "header": "Anticipated Results",
            "content": "Treatment with DMSO activates the retinoblastoma \\(Rb) protein and  improves efficiencies of differentiation into a desired lineage from any pluripotent stem cell line.  Most importantly, this treatment improves the capacity for terminal differentiation into functional cell types both in vitro and in vivo."
        }
    ],
